description:
&lt;p&gt;The Medicines Management directorate has an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and committed Pharmacist to join the Cwm Taf Morgannwg University Health Board pharmacy team. The post holder will be based at the Princess of Wales Hospital in Bridgend.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will provide an exciting opportunity to build on your previous pharmacy experience and to enhance your clinical knowledge and medicines management skills. Successful candidates will rotate through a range of specialities providing a clinical pharmacy service to many areas including Medicine, Acute Medicine, Medicines Information, Surgery, Paediatrics and Mental Health. The rotations provide the opportunity to broaden your portfolio and strengthen your future career prospects in a dynamic setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The pharmacy department at POW is a modern, friendly department which hosts many pharmacist independent prescribers. The post holder will work closely with the clinical pharmacy team, and be supported by the Patient Services Lead Pharmacist to continue to develop in their pharmacy practice skills and knowledge. The successful candidate will possess excellent communication skills and be able to work well as part of a multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The directorate is forward thinking and innovative, having an integrated approach to Primary and Secondary Care management of medicines. The hospital site has automated pharmacy systems, comprehensive medicines management services and fully implemented electronic discharge systems. Pharmacist-led clinics are well established and Pharmacists are valued members of clinical multidisciplinary teams in both Primary and Secondary Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are fully committed to personal development and advanced practice, encouraging all staff to undertake relevant education and training to meet their needs. The post holder will have opportunities to undertake the Pharmacist Independent Prescribing course and will be supported to develop both clinically and strategically.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Princess of Wales Hospital is located off the M4 in Bridgend, with easy access from both the West and the East corners of Wales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speaking applicants are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Application Closing date: 17th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eleri Schiavone&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Patient Services Lead Pharmacist&lt;br /&gt;Tel: 01656 752686&lt;/p&gt;
